article.description: Robert Hatter scored 28 of his 32 points in the second half to help Cornell come back and edge Siena 81-80 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Cornell comes back to edge Siena 81-80
article.linkText: Cornell comes back to edge Siena 81-80
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Robert Hatter scored 28 of his 32 points in the second half to help Cornell come back and edge Siena 81-80 on Tuesday night. Hatter was 10 of 20 from the floor, made four 3-pointers, and had six assists and three steals for the Big Red (4-4), who is undefeated at home. Marquis Wright had 19 points to lead Siena (4-3). Javion Ogunyemi scored 17 points, and Brett Bisping added 16 points with 18 rebounds. Lavon Long made a 3-pointer to give the Saints a 60-50 lead with nine minutes left. Hatter scored 19 points during a 27-17 Big Red surge, including three 3-pointers, to tie it at 77 with 53 seconds left. The Saints then made 3 of 4 field goals, and Hatter and Darryl Smith each made a pair of free throws for an 81-77 lead with three seconds left. Siena's Ryan Oliver made a 3-poiniter at the buzzer.
